The paper deals with the complexity and approximability of the constraint satisfaction problem (CSP) and its extension, the promise CSP (PCSP). This falls under the area of computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses algebraic methods, which are commonly used in graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.GT, cs.LO).
